rComments: Even though I got an A in this class, I had had to work for that grade. A lot of reading, but he is very fair and tells you what will be on the test. He is good at explaining material, because the textbook can be confusing. So if you don't attend class, you will not do well. If you actually try, you can get a good grade.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Clear grading criteria', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Loved Psycholinguistics with Professor Chandan. He was very straightforward in what would be on the test. If you attend every lecture and put in the time, you will get a good mark.

Dr. Narayan is a great lecturer and he explains the concepts in a way that is easy to understand. I took his class in the summer and found his tests to be very fair. Most of the test material were from lectures. So as long as you take detailed lecture notes, you should be able to get A/A+ in his class.

His lectures are incredibly engaging and efficient, and he is always happy to answer our questions.  His tests and exams are tricky so make sure you read the questions carefully before answering, but they are definitely fair and doable if you study. Attending class is the best way to get n A because he explains concepts better than the textbook!

Great lecturer, students are always engaged, content & responsive. Powerpoints are clear and do a good job of summarizing parts of the textbook that will be tested. Only negative is that his tests are tricky and I often did worse than what I thought I did even after studying notes and textbook. But nonetheless got an A & would recommend this class
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Respected', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Course code was also LING 3220, Dr. Narayan was amazing! I really want to take another one of his classes. Lectures were always interesting and concise. Tests are all straight from lecture notes, so attending class is crucial because he better explains concepts. Really enjoyed the class and would definitely recommend it.

At first the material is dense, especially for psychology students, but his lectures are fantastic.  The topics are really fascinating and follow a nice flow (not lingering on certain areas). This is a great overview of linguistics and is easily the most interesting class I took this year. Great material. Great prof.
Professor Narayan is an amazing professor. He brings humor into his lectures to make the course fun and engaging. He is very approachable and his lecture slides were easy to follow and crystal clear.
Nice prof and very helpful during office hours. His lectures/slides are very clear and explains them well.

This professor is passionate, clear, and can inject the right amount of humour when necessary. Please be advised: For those liberal arts students looking to take an "easy" elective, this course will require work and attention. The structure is more science than theory. For those willing to work, Professor Narayan is the best in the business.

The course is a breeze. Material is easy. TAs are helpful. However, this prof is an outright nightmare. I needed to speak with him in person and I couldn't attend normal office hours. He basically said either attend his office hours or don't bother. Totally rude and disrespectful to students. This guy needs to learn about a thing called "empathy."

Best prof! lectures are a must! very clearly explains slides, slides are straightforward but he goes through a lot of helpful examples. Content in class is straightforward if assignments are done. He's very understanding and tries to help students to the best of his ability. NOT an easy 4.0 unless your willing to put the effort in.

Worts professor in the world. Does not have the right email address listed on the UTSC Linguistics web page. I took the online version of the course that does not require you to be there, but there was no helpful guides as to where to go to access the videos (it wasnt posted on the intranet or the blackboard). No course outlines posted. Failure.
Really nice, appreciates humour, and interaction (as long as it's productive). His notes and slides are super productive as well. Class attendance is key!
Never replies emails, marks you wrong when your knowledge level is beyond course material. Doesn't take students seriously.
He's great!

Quizzes, problem sets and exams are extremely easy. Interesting lectures, lectures cover almost everything in the textbook, reading is almost unnecessary, unless you plan on skipping every class, then you have to read, but its still easy if you do that.

Interesting class, assigned homework is really useful and helps you to understand the material better. Approachable prof, really nice and willing to help students. Definitely one of my favourite classes & profs so far

I'm surprised to see so much negativity about this prof here! I think he's one of the "cool" profs. He's young and funny and very easy going. I think he does slack off a bit sometimes, as ALL of the 2 hour lectures for LINA02 were ended 30min early. However, his style of teaching is quite clear and is not boring. I'd take more courses with  him

He doesn't care about his work or students; chain smoker, saw him smoking outside during an exam last year. Not open to opinions, when he was told that someone cried after the final he said those were crocodile tears (his original words).

I found Professor Narayan to be quite helpful and quite enjoyable in lecture. Aside from the fact that he goes verbatim off the slide, he is quite interesting and if you express interest, he'll explain further. He does have an air of pretension though, and I've found that he doesn't always treat all students the same way.
rude. completely not helpful. thinks he is funny when he is not. most likely the worst teacher i have ever had. doesn't care about students

The professor is enthusiast about the course, however always cancels class and is no help! He does not answer emails nor clarify questions. He is of no great assistance so far when it comes to the project worth 50% of your mark. He is also very unorganized.

the tutorial is useless. they teach you the stuff after you hand in the assignment.As for the final exam, i thought i got a decent mark but wait till you see your final mark. its totally different from what you had imagine. The lectures is alright, but the materials r hard to absorbed.

VERY BORING TEACHER! going to lectures is completely useless because all he does is ramble on about stuff on the slides and it seems like everything he says is useless/he has been talking about it for like 5 minutes already. However, he is a substitute for this course.. but still, very boring teacher.. i stopped going to lectures half way through

At first I thought he was ridicoulous as a prof, he read of the slides, couldn't answer students' questions, stuttering alot, and the exam was purly textbook based. But then I realized he was subbing in for the psych prof who teaches this course. He is very down to earth and approchable (hard to believe he's over 30). He tries his best.

I love this prof! He's so cool, and he's really funny sometimes... can be a bit harsh though, when he singles people out for talking/ sleeping in class (especially since you have to go to class for clicker questions!). It's a cool subject though and he teaches it well, and it's not too hard. Oh and his slide notes are very helpful- study those!
Strict, has excellent class control. Despite this, he can genuinely make you laugh when you least expect it. Material presented clearly and use of international examples a great asset.
He's very strict and loves it when students follow rules. Excellent prof.
Very easy marking for this class, and very fair as a professor. also FYI, the LINA01 lecture notes he used were actually borrowed from the previous year's prof
Very easy prof. listens to students. Had him for this class and was very fair.
Narayan was a total cutie! However, I really disliked this class. Material is not easy, however his lecture slides are helpful and detailed.

He has the most adorable face ever, and with what a grace he carries himself.. Great course, and real fun to attend his lectures. Kind of looked forward to it, even when his lectures were late i.e. after 5:00 pm. Very organized and HOTTEST prof ever ... :-)

Prof. Narayan is adorable!! He has an amazing sense of style and an amazing face to go along with it. Lecture notes are very helpful and he goes through the course material in meticulous detail. Overall great prof.

Excellent prof! i really enjoyed his class. He explains the material really well. Very helful during office hours. He is very organized and lectures are interesting. I would recommend taking his class.

first i would like to say he the the HOTTEST PROFESSOR IN UOFT! and second i took linguistics with him and loved his class. very helpful, always nice, a great personality, always willing to help, and never moody. he's great i loved his class..and i went to every class too!
Excellent prof. Very helpful if you attend his office hours. Approachable. 1st half of course OK, 2nd half harder. Watch out for final.
